  "prompt": "How do I get over a crush on my guy best friend?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to help you move on:\n\n1. Acknowledge your feelings\n- Accept that these feelings exist\n- Don't judge yourself for having them\n\n2. Create some emotional distance\n- Limit one-on-one time temporarily\n- Focus on other friendships and activities\n- Avoid romanticizing the friendship\n\n3. Keep yourself busy\n- Pursue hobbies and interests\n- Spend time with other friends\n- Meet new people\n- Focus on personal growth\n\n4. Consider dating other people\n- Open yourself to new romantic possibilities\n- Don't wait around for something that might not happen\n\n5. Be honest with yourself\n- Evaluate if staying close friends is healthy for you\n- Decide if you need space to heal\n\n6. Process your emotions\n- Talk to trusted friends or family\n- Consider journaling\n- Practice self-care\n\n7. If needed, have an honest conversation\n- If the friendship feels too complicated, discuss boundaries\n- Be prepared for potential outcomes\n\n8. Give yourself time to heal\n- Moving on takes patience\n- Don't rush the process\n- Be kind to yourself\n\nRemember that your feelings are valid, and it's okay to prioritize your emotional well-being.",
